":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Morville","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English:  see  Moorfield  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Moorfield","meanings":["English: locative name from Morville (Shrops), which is recorded as  <i>Mamerfeld</i> in the 12th century,  <i>Momerefeld</i> in 1255, and  <i>Morfelde</i> in 1464."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When William de Morville was born in 1109, in Valognes, Manche, Normandy, France, his father, Richard de Morville, was 18 and his mother, unknown, was 19. He married Matilda de Moreville in 1144, in Dorset, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1161, in Bridport, Dorset, England, at the age of 52."},"et":{"1109–1161":"1109–1161","1128–1160":"1128–1160","1125–1170":"1125–1170","1150–1202":"1150–1202","1091–1154":"1091–1154","1091–Female":"1091–Surnud","1091":"1091","1128":"1128","1202":"1202","1125":"1125","1144":"1144","1154":"1154","1150":"1150","about 1154":"umbes 1154","1161":"1161","1160":"1160","1109":"1109","1170":"1170","Pentney, Norfolk, England":"Pentney, Norfolk, England","Bridport, Dorset, England":"Bridport, Dorset, England","Valognes, Manche, Lower Normandy, France":"Valognes, Manche, Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Wraxall, Somerset, England":"Wraxall, Somerset, England","Dorset, England":"Dorset, England"},"fi":{"1109–1161":"1109–1161","1128–1160":"1128–1160","1125–1170":"1125–1170","1150–1202":"1150–1202","1091–1154":"1091–1154","1091–Female":"1091–Kuollut","1091":"1091","1128":"1128","1202":"1202","1125":"1125","1144":"1144","1154":"1154","1150":"1150","about 1154":"noin 1154","1161":"1161","1160":"1160","1109":"1109","1170":"1170","Pentney, Norfolk, England":"Pentney, Norfolk, England","Bridport, Dorset, England":"Bridport, Dorset, England","Valognes, Manche, Lower Normandy, France":"Valognes, Manche, Normandie, Ranska","Wraxall, Somerset, England":"Wraxall, Somerset, England","Dorset, England":"Dorset, England"},"fr":{"1109–1161":"1109–1161","1128–1160":"1128–1160","1125–1170":"1125–1170","1150–1202":"1150–1202","1091–1154":"1091–1154","1091–Female":"1091–Décédée","1091":"1091","1128":"1128","1202":"1202","1125":"1125","1144":"1144","1154":"1154","1150":"1150","about 1154":"environ 1154","1161":"1161","1160":"1160","1109":"1109","1170":"1170","Pentney, Norfolk, England":"Pentney, Norfolk, Angleterre","Bridport, Dorset, England":"Bridport, Dorset, Angleterre","Valognes, Manche, Lower Normandy, France":"Valognes, Manche, Normandie, France","Wraxall, Somerset, England":"W